name: oslo.concurrency
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "oslo.concurrency" %}
{% set version = "5.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9f46946e9f8a72a06f14fe3dc4189a4d3dd39862831525393a3119bdbbe7897e

build:
  number: 0
  script: '{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv '
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - pbr !=2.1.0,>=2.0.0
    - pip
    - python >=3.8
  run:
    - pbr !=2.1.0,>=2.0.0
    - oslo.config >=5.2.0
    - oslo.i18n >=3.15.3
    - oslo.utils >=3.33.0
    - fasteners >=0.7.0
    - python >=3.8

test:
  imports:
    - oslo_concurrency
    - oslo_concurrency.lockutils
    - oslo_concurrency.opts
    - oslo_concurrency.processutils
    - oslo_concurrency.version
    - oslo_concurrency.watchdog

about:
  home: https://docs.openstack.org/oslo.concurrency/latest/
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: The oslo.concurrency library has utilities for safely running multi-thread, multi-process applications using locking mechanisms and for running external processes

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pg-hbk
    - sy-hbk
    - tschoonj
